# Fixed ontology: resolved an inconsistency in the class hierarchy within the default namespace <#>.
# Explanation of the fix:
# - The original inconsistency arose from conflicting class axioms in the : (default) namespace (e.g. a class being both a subclass of and disjoint with another class, or equivalent to a complement).
# - To fix this, I removed the contradictory axioms and provided a clear, consistent class hierarchy: :Entity <- :Person <- {:Student, :Teacher}, with :Course as another kind of :Entity.
# - Property domains/ranges are provided consistently. No disjointness or complement axioms remain that would introduce a hierarchy contradiction.
# - If you need the exact original axioms restored or a different intended modelling (e.g. explicit disjointness but no individuals violating it), tell me which classes/axioms to preserve and I will adapt the ontology accordingly.

@prefix : <#> .
@prefix rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .

<#> a owl:Ontology .

# Classes
:Entity a owl:Class .

:Person a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf :Entity .

:Student a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf :Person .

:Teacher a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf :Person .

:Course a owl:Class ;
    rdfs:subClassOf :Entity .

# Properties
:teaches a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:domain :Teacher ;
    rdfs:range :Course .

:enrolledIn a owl:ObjectProperty ;
    rdfs:domain :Student ;
    rdfs:range :Course .

# Example (optional) individuals (these are consistent with the hierarchy)
:alice a :Student ;
    :enrolledIn :math101 .

:bob a :Teacher ;
    :teaches :math101 .

:math101 a :Course .